                    "description": "Lead and manage bids in the European, Australian and New Zealand area for own products (e.g. SOTAS vehicle systems), communication products from the Thales group (e.g. radios, SATCOM systems), security solutions, system integration and product/solution related services offerings. Since 2016 my main areas of focus are the Dutch and German defence markets. Bid sizes range from 500k to 50M\nMain responsibilities are: \n-\tLead identification and qualification\n-\tCapturing support, including product demo\u2019s\n-\tBid qualification after receipt of RfI/RfP/RfQ\n-\tDefine proposal strategy (together with capture leader and bid team)\n-\tLeading and coordinating the bidteam\n-\tDefine WBS, PBS and estimation breakdown \n-\tInitiate and consolidate cost estimates\n-\tCoordinate, co-write and review proposals\n-\tArrange all internal process validations (design, legal, finance, export control, HSE, offset, etc)\n-\tInitiate and manage risk & opportunity register for bid and future project\n-\tLead internal review meetings\n-\tPlan, organize and prepare formal offer approval meeting\n-\tParticipate and/or support contract negotiations\n-\tPlan, organize and prepare formal contract approval meeting\n-\tOrganize and perform hand-over contract and all related files to project team\n-\tManage bid costs\n-\tInitiate and perform win/loss analysis and lessons learned sessions\n\nAdditional formal roles (next to my bid manager job):\n\u2022\tDomain process owner for the Manage Bid process:  responsible of the proper application of the defined Manage Bid process within our local domain/entity. This includes, amongst others identifying and initiating (local) process improvements, training and coaching of new colleague and implementing process changes and instructions, defined by Corporate in our local domain/entity.  \n\u2022\tSales Operations Manager; the local administrator tasks of the Oracle Siebel CRM/order intake forecast tool and the facilitating/enabling the yearly formal budgeting process wrt expected order intake",
